article.headline: CS Northridge 68, E. Washington 59
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. -- Lenny Daniel scored 19 points and Rashaun McLemore added 15 as Cal State Northridge defeated Eastern Washington 68-59 in a BracketBuster game on Saturday night. Daniel had 11 rebounds for the Matadors (11-16). Glen Dena had 17 points, Cliff Colimon 14 and Jeffery Forbes 10 for the Eagles (8-18). McLemore scored 13 of his points in the second half, when Daniel played just nine minutes because of foul trouble. Eastern Washington trailed by 11 in the second half but cut the lead to 52-50 with 8:54 remaining. However, McLemore scored seven points, including a 3-pointer, to key an 11-2 surge that enabled the Matadors to pull away.
